  <caaml:metaData>
    <caaml:comment>After a dry and mild fall, Montana and Idaho entered winter, receiving 70-100cms (2-3 feet) of snow in the past 5 days in the Lost Trail Pass area. The storm has settled well most locations, however there is a layer of concern on steeper, shaded, northerly aspects above 7500'. Test results showed propagation around a meter down in two study pits 145cm deep (ECTP22 @47cm SC/Q1; ECTP28@47cm SC/Q1). &#13;
Though generally conditions are good, keep an eye on those slopes. &#13;
And be aware, early season conditions still persist !</caaml:comment>
